::'''Dunn:''' ...I certainly get your point, Gilbert. But this medal of merit is not something I can give to anyone I want.
::'''Dunn:''' How long have you been in the army, twenty years? Thirty years? Don't you understand this...
::'''Gilbert:''' Dunn, I took special care of you when you were a new recruit. Now that you've become a captain, how come you are putting on airs with me?
::'''Gilbert:''' Can't you do me this tiny little favor? Do you want to see me getting laughed at by my wife and daughter...?
::'''Dunn:''' I've told you many times. It's a matter of principle...
::'''Dunn:''' ...Ah, right on time, here comes (Trailblazer)! What do you make of his request?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_301110201_14-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_301110201_14-->
::----
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Actually, I don't want to meddle...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110309-->
:::'''Dunn:''' ...Come on now, you never shy away from giving people a little help.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_301110311-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What happened?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110311-->
::'''Dunn:''' Do you know Gilbert? Yes, him, the oldest logistics officer in the restricted zone.
::'''Dunn:''' He's about to retire. The way I see it, he should spend the last few months doing what he's been doing and return to the city to reunite with his wife and daughter when he finally retires...
::'''Dunn:''' But he wants to ask an unreasonable favor from me at a time like this! The geezer wants to borrow a medal of merit, just to look good in front of his family. You tell me, is that reasonable?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_301110201_22-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_301110201_22-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Can't you just lend him the medal?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110315-->
:::'''Dunn:''' Of course not! What do you think the rules of the Silvermane Guards are for?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} True... It doesn't sound very appropriate.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110317-->
:::'''Dunn:''' See, old man! Even (Trailblazer) said so.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_301110318-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110318-->
::'''Dunn:''' Besides, don't you have the Veteran Guard Medal from your twentieth anniversary? Isn't that enough honor for you to show off...
::'''Gilbert:''' Youngster, why don't you understand... You can get one of these just by staying long enough. It is not considered an honor. And it won't bring me any respect...
::'''Dunn:''' *sigh* You just don't get it, do you?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_301110201_31-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_301110201_31-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Can I help with anything?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110322-->
:::'''Dunn:''' Yeah, let me think about it...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why is no one giving me any medal?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110324-->
:::'''Dunn:''' ...Remember that time you knocked me out? Consider yourself lucky that you're not sent to court-martial yet, let alone getting a medal...
:::'''Dunn:''' Wait, you reminded me...
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_301110326-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_301110326-->
::'''Dunn:''' Yes, I have a good idea!
::'''Dunn:''' I heard that another automaton "Grizzly" has lost control recently, and is still roaming and wreaking havoc in the restricted zone. Now that there is a shortage of personnel, my subordinates can only maintain control in the surrounding area temporarily and they dare not act rashly.
::'''Dunn:''' (Trailblazer), can you take the old man to deal with this problem? When this is done, I can give the credit to Gilbert.
::'''Gilbert:''' Wh&mdash;what a great opportunity! {{MC|f=Young lady|m=Young man}}, let's go and take a look!
