:::{{DIcon|Talk}} How's your holiday been?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504049203-->
::::'''Gilbert:''' The first few days were tough. I kept waking up before dawn, as if I was still on the front lines, automatically checking supplies, only to be laughed at by my wife...
::::'''Gilbert:''' Life at home is truly blissful, complete with delicious meals, the warmth of a Geomarrow furnace, and loving family members. Even just lounging in a chair and reading the newspaper all day feels perfect.
::::'''Gilbert:''' I'm eagerly anticipating my next vacation, and to make it arrive sooner, I'm committed to working harder at my job.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} What have you been up to lately?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029619-->
::::'''Gilbert:''' Same old, same old. Ore pack inspection, maintaining armaments&mdash;stuff like that.
::::'''Gilbert:''' I used to think that these jobs were boring as heck... Now I've finally let that go and I find them more interesting.
::::'''Gilbert:''' It's all thanks to you. If you hadn't helped me communicate with my daughter, I would still be in a slump... Thank you so much!
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} What's interesting lately?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029623-->
::::'''Gilbert:''' Interesting? Honestly, nothing. Apart from logistics and front-line battles, there is not much going on in the restricted zone... Every day is basically the same.
::::'''Gilbert:''' ... Ah, I got one. Two days ago, Dunn... Do you know Dunn? The young man with a high rank, that's in charge of the restricted zone. You know he used to be in a band, right?
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I've had dealings with him.
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Who's that?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029627-->
:::::'''Gilbert:''' ...You don't know? Huh, no big deal. He is just a young officer who once played in a band.
:::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_501029628-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029628-->
::::'''Gilbert:''' I'll go on. Two days ago, Dunn played his guitar as usual, and Officer Gepard came to the rear for a routine inspection... Guess what happened?
::::'''Gilbert:''' He forgot to put the guitar away that day!
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Music isn't allowed in the military?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029630-->
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} ...What's wrong with that?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029631-->
::::'''Gilbert:''' It's okay to entertain yourself in the restricted zone, but neglecting your responsibilities while on duty is a major offense.
::::'''Gilbert:''' There is a member in his squad who always takes the blame for him. His name is Zackery, I think? Anyway, that day, Dunn blamed it on Zackery again.
::::'''Gilbert:''' When Gepard saw the guitar, he asked, "Whose is this?" Right after speaking, Zackery stepped forward and said: "Sir, it's mine!"
::::'''Gilbert:''' You'll never guess what happened next! Gepard asked the boy to play something, right there on the spot!
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_501029601_21-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_501029601_21-->
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Oh boy.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029639-->
:::::'''Gilbert:''' It scared the heck out of Zackery. I heard that his legs were shaking uncontrollably. Hahaha!
:::::'''Gilbert:''' So Dunn had to give himself up. Luckily, officer Gepard is a lenient man. He let it go.
:::::'''Gilbert:''' I heard that they knew each other... Hmmm, who knows what's true!?
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} He got him there.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029638-->
:::::'''Gilbert:''' That's right!
:::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_501029639-->
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029639-->
:::::'''Gilbert:''' It scared the heck out of Zackery. I heard that his legs were shaking uncontrollably. Hahaha!
:::::'''Gilbert:''' So Dunn had to give himself up. Luckily, officer Gepard is a lenient man. He let it go.
:::::'''Gilbert:''' I heard that they knew each other... Hmmm, who knows what's true!?
