:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Have you been back home yet?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029605-->
::::'''Gilbert:''' Not yet...
::::'''Gilbert:''' But I've applied for a few days off to visit my family, and I think it will be approved since I solved the Malfunctioning Robot problem.
::::'''Gilbert:''' Once I get back home, I must apologize to my wife and my daughter...
::::'''Gilbert:''' *Sigh* I'm getting a little nervous. My heart is beating so fast... Finally, I am going to get to visit them, but why am I so scared?
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Enjoy your father-daughter time with Lila!
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029610-->
:::::'''Gilbert:''' You're right. She's a big girl now and we've never really talked...
:::::'''Gilbert:''' I feel like I was asking for trouble by keeping everything to myself. Maybe all those problems could have been solved if I had just talked to my family...
:::::'''Gilbert:''' You too should talk to your friends or family about any confusion you feel inside! Don't keep everything to yourself as I did. It almost ruined my life.
:::::'''Gilbert:''' This is coming from an old man, who knows from experience. Hahahaha!
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Eating a home-cooked meal is indeed a fortunate thing.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501029615-->
:::::'''Gilbert:''' Yes! You are making me hungry. Hahaha.
:::::'''Gilbert:''' My wife's cooking skills... aren't great. But after all this time, I've come to really love and look forward to that weird-smelling home-cooked aroma...
:::::'''Gilbert:''' You have to come to my place someday to try her cooking. Haha!
